 profits by indirect involvement: freedmen, municipal notables, and "friends" often served as the equivalent of partners or agents of aristocrats with large holdings in land. In demonstrating a flexibility in upper-class attitudes toward commercial activity, he offers a study in the adaptation of a social system to economic realities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCommerce. 0aGeschichte. 0aHandel, Kommunikation, Verkehr. 0aHandel. 0aRomeinse rijk. 0aSocial classes. 0aSociale klassen. 0aSozialgeschichte. 4aHISTORY / General. 4aRome -- Commerce -- History. 4aSocial classes -- Rome -- History. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Complete eBook Packagez9783110353488oZDB-23-HCO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: World History eBook Packagez9783110353563oZDB-23-HWH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z97831104422120 cprintz978067433118140uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067433119840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674331198423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674331198/original  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-HCO  aZDB-23-HWH